{
  "texts": [
    "In their study, two models were evaluated: a traditional MLP with hand-crafted features and a CNN with the same MLP structure for classification.",
    "The assessment was carried out on the CMATERDB 3.3.1 database, revealing that CNN outperformed the MLP, achieving a 4.1% increase in accuracy.",
    "These findings confirm the efficacy of CNNs in feature extraction compared to traditional handcrafted methods.The same CNN architecture [70] underwent further improvement in another study by Ashiquzzaman et al. [71].",
    "In this enhancement, the authors incorporated data augmentation techniques, introduced the dropout effect, and changed the activation function.",
    "Addressing the limitation of the ReLU function, which can halt learning in regions where x is negative due to its derivative being 0, the authors opted for the Exponential Linear Unit (ELU) function."
  ]
}